11 review and comment on the proposed increase at one or more meetings held at a time and
12 place of convenience to the public in each county in which the increase is proposed to be
13 implemented.
14 (ii) At least 10 working days before the start of the first meeting
15 under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph, the Authority shall provide to the public on the
16 Authority’s official website the proposed increase in tolls, fees, mileage rate ranges, pricing
17 periods, toll zones, or other charges and information and studies used in its analysis to
18 justify the proposed increase.
19 (iii) For a period of at least 10 working days after the last scheduled
20 meeting for public review and comment under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph, the
21 Authority shall provide the public with an opportunity to submit additional written
22 comments on the proposal.
23 (iv) Within 10 days after the close of the written comment period
24 under subparagraph (iii) of this paragraph, the Authority shall provide to the public on its
25 official website and to the members of the Authority a summary and analysis of the
26 comments received from the public on the proposal.
27 (4) Before the Authority votes on any proposal to increase tolls, fees, or
28 other charges on any part of a fixed toll transportation facilities project or votes on an
29 increase in mileage rate ranges, pricing periods, toll zones, fees, or other charges on any
30 part of a variably priced toll transportation facilities project, the Authority shall:
31 (i) Provide in writing to all of the members of the Authority and, on
32 request, to the public any recommendation of the Authority regarding the proposal;
33 (ii) For a period of at least 10 working days after making any
34 recommendation on the proposal, provide an opportunity for public review and written
35 comment on the recommendation;
36 (iii) Provide to the public on its official website:

